wwpEnvironMIB.name: wwpEnvironMIB

revisions.description: Updated the battery status. Added the four notifications for the battery state change. The new added notification wwpEnvPortalPowerSourceNotification replaces the wwpEnvPowerSwitchNotification.
Changed the temperature thresholds to be read-write. Added Battery States and updated the notification for the battery states. Added dry contact, door and RF notifications.

wwpEnvironMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpEnvironMIB.description: The MIB module for the WWP Specifc environment. It contains the environment variables for the WWP System.

PortList.name: PortList
PortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

wwpEnvBattStatus.name: wwpEnvBattStatus
wwpEnvBattStatus.description: Describes the battery hardware the device is configured with. For Portals, the Management station should use the new added object wwpEnvPortalCurrentBattStatus for the batery status.

wwpEnvPowerTable.name: wwpEnvPowerTable
wwpEnvPowerTable.description: A list of power supply entries.

wwpEnvPowerEntry.name: wwpEnvPowerEntry
wwpEnvPowerEntry.description: An entry in the powerTable providing objects for a power supply.

wwpEnvPowerSupplyRedundancy.name: wwpEnvPowerSupplyRedundancy
wwpEnvPowerSupplyRedundancy.description: Denotes whether or not the power supply is redundant.

wwpEnvRedPowerSupplyNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvRedPowerSupplyNotifEnabled
wwpEnvRedPowerSupplyNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpEnvRedPowerSupplyNotification. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvFanModuleTable.name: wwpEnvFanModuleTable
wwpEnvFanModuleTable.description: A list of fan module entries.

wwpEnvFanModuleEntry.name: wwpEnvFanModuleEntry
wwpEnvFanModuleEntry.description: An entry in the fan module Table providing objects for a fan module.

wwpEnvFanAvgSpeed.name: wwpEnvFanAvgSpeed
wwpEnvFanAvgSpeed.description: The fans average speed in RPM. The average is calculated on a continuous basis from system startup.

wwpEnvFanCurrentSpeed.name: wwpEnvFanCurrentSpeed
wwpEnvFanCurrentSpeed.description: The current speed of the fan in RPM.

wwpEnvFanMinSpeed.name: wwpEnvFanMinSpeed
wwpEnvFanMinSpeed.description: The minimum speed of the fan in RPM.

wwpEnvFanModuleNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvFanModuleNotifEnabled
wwpEnvFanModuleNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpEnvFanModuleNotification. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvTempSensorTable.name: wwpEnvTempSensorTable
wwpEnvTempSensorTable.description: A list of Temp Sensors entries.

wwpEnvTempSensorEntry.name: wwpEnvTempSensorEntry
wwpEnvTempSensorEntry.description: An entry in the Temp Sensor Table providing objects for a Temp Sensor.

wwpEnvTempSensorValue.name: wwpEnvTempSensorValue
wwpEnvTempSensorValue.description: The value of temperature measured by the sensor inside the device in degrees C.

wwpEnvTempSensorHighThreshold.name: wwpEnvTempSensorHighThreshold
wwpEnvTempSensorHighThreshold.description: The highest value that the object wwpEnvTempSensorValue may obtain at which a wwpEnvMIBTempNotification is sent.

wwpEnvTempSensorLowThreshold.name: wwpEnvTempSensorLowThreshold
wwpEnvTempSensorLowThreshold.description: The Lowest value that the object wwpEnvTempSensorValue may obtain at which a wwpEnvMIBTempNotification is sent.

wwpEnvTempSensorState.name: wwpEnvTempSensorState
wwpEnvTempSensorState.description: The state indicates whether the current temp is greater than, equal to or less than the threshold state.

wwpEnvTempNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvTempNotifEnabled
wwpEnvTempNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpEnvTempNotification. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpPortPowerMgmtTable.name: wwpPortPowerMgmtTable
wwpPortPowerMgmtTable.description: A list of Port Power Management entries. This table affects the port power only when the input power supply is Battery.

wwpPortPowerMgmtEntry.name: wwpPortPowerMgmtEntry
wwpPortPowerMgmtEntry.description: An entry in the Port Power Mgmt Table providing objects for Port Power Management.

wwpEnvPortBankId.name: wwpEnvPortBankId
wwpEnvPortBankId.description: Denotes the Port Bank module. A Bank is a set of ports for the power management when the source of the input power is switched to battery.

wwpEnvPortMap.name: wwpEnvPortMap
wwpEnvPortMap.description: The port map associated with this BankId.

wwpEnvPortBankOn.name: wwpEnvPortBankOn
wwpEnvPortBankOn.description: The object to decide whether the port related to this Bank should be on or not if the input power supply is switched to Battery.

wwpPowerSwitchingOp.name: wwpPowerSwitchingOp
wwpPowerSwitchingOp.description: The object to notify whether the input power supply is switching from ac to Battery or vice versa.

wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatus.name: wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatus
wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatus.description: Describes the current status of the battery. If battery is connected then the status is indicated as 'present'.

wwpEnvPortalBatteryVoltageLevel.name: wwpEnvPortalBatteryVoltageLevel
wwpEnvPortalBatteryVoltageLevel.description: Describes the current voltage level of the battery.

wwpEnvPortalBatteryCondition.name: wwpEnvPortalBatteryCondition
wwpEnvPortalBatteryCondition.description: Describes the current condition of the battery.

wwpEnvPortalPowerSource.name: wwpEnvPortalPowerSource
wwpEnvPortalPowerSource.description: Describes the current power source for the device.

wwpEnvBatteryNormalStateName.name: wwpEnvBatteryNormalStateName
wwpEnvBatteryNormalStateName.description: The state name associated with the low state of the battery.

wwpEnvBatteryLowStateName.name: wwpEnvBatteryLowStateName
wwpEnvBatteryLowStateName.description: The state name associated with the normal state of the battery.

wwpEnvBatteryGoodStateName.name: wwpEnvBatteryGoodStateName
wwpEnvBatteryGoodStateName.description: The state name associated with the good state of the battery.

wwpEnvBatteryBadStateName.name: wwpEnvBatteryBadStateName
wwpEnvBatteryBadStateName.description: The state name associated with the bad state of the battery.

wwpEnvBatteryPresentStateName.name: wwpEnvBatteryPresentStateName
wwpEnvBatteryPresentStateName.description: The state name associated with the battery state 'present'.

wwpEnvBatteryMissingStateName.name: wwpEnvBatteryMissingStateName
wwpEnvBatteryMissingStateName.description: The state name associated with the battery state 'missing'.

wwpEnvBatteryPowerPrimaryStateName.name: wwpEnvBatteryPowerPrimaryStateName
wwpEnvBatteryPowerPrimaryStateName.description: The state name associated with the state when the device is on primary power.

wwpEnvBatteryPowerBatteryStateName.name: wwpEnvBatteryPowerBatteryStateName
wwpEnvBatteryPowerBatteryStateName.description: The state name associated with the state when the device is on battery power.

wwpEnvBatteryLowStateNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvBatteryLowStateNotifEnabled
wwpEnvBatteryLowStateNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system will generate the wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatusNotification in case of battery state changing from normal to low or vice versa. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvBatteryBadStateNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvBatteryBadStateNotifEnabled
wwpEnvBatteryBadStateNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system will generate the wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatusNotification in case of battery state changing from good to bad or vice versa. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvBatteryMissingStateNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvBatteryMissingStateNotifEnabled
wwpEnvBatteryMissingStateNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system will generate the wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatusNotification in case of battery state changing from present to missing or vice versa. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvBatteryPowerNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvBatteryPowerNotifEnabled
wwpEnvBatteryPowerNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system will generate the wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatusNotification in case of input power changing from primary to battery or vice versa. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvBatteryPeriodicTrapsTimer.name: wwpEnvBatteryPeriodicTrapsTimer
wwpEnvBatteryPeriodicTrapsTimer.description: Adjusts the amount of time, in hours, when the current state of the battery is evaluated and status traps are automatically issued. When set to zero (0) no periodic evaluation of the battery is performed.

wwpEnvBatteryPowerUpTrapsEnable.name: wwpEnvBatteryPowerUpTrapsEnable
wwpEnvBatteryPowerUpTrapsEnable.description: When set to true, upon portal power-up the state of the battery is evaluated and status traps are issued. When set to false, no portal power-up battery state traps will be issued.

wwpEnvDoorNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvDoorNotifEnabled
wwpEnvDoorNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpEnvDoorStateChgNotification. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateName.name: wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateName
wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateName.description: The state name associated with the open state of the dry contact.

wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateChgAccumulate.name: wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateChgAccumulate
wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateChgAccumulate.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will cause the system to accumulate open state changes.

wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateCount.name: wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateCount
wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateCount.description: The number of times the dry contact has entered the open state.

wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateNotifEnabled
wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateNotification. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateName.name: wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateName
wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateName.description: The state name associated with the close state of the dry contact.

wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateChgAccumulate.name: wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateChgAccumulate
wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateChgAccumulate.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will cause the system to accumulate close state changes.

wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateCount.name: wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateCount
wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateCount.description: The number of times the dry contact has entered the close state.

wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateNotifEnabled.name: wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateNotifEnabled
wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateNotification. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpEnvRFModuleState.name: wwpEnvRFModuleState
wwpEnvRFModuleState.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will set the the RF state to 'enable'.

wwpEnvRFModuleSignalDetect.name: wwpEnvRFModuleSignalDetect
wwpEnvRFModuleSignalDetect.description: The status of signal detect by the RF Module.

wwpEnvPowerSupplyStatusNotification.name: wwpEnvPowerSupplyStatusNotification
wwpEnvPowerSupplyStatusNotification.description: A wwpEnvPowerSupplyStatusNotification is sent if a power supply state is changed.

wwpEnvFanModuleNotification.name: wwpEnvFanModuleNotification
wwpEnvFanModuleNotification.description: A wwpEnvFanModuleNotification is sent if the fan state changes.

wwpEnvTempNotification.name: wwpEnvTempNotification
wwpEnvTempNotification.description: A wwpEnvTempNotification is sent if the wwpEnvTempSensorState is changed.

wwpEnvPowerSwitchNotification.name: wwpEnvPowerSwitchNotification
wwpEnvPowerSwitchNotification.description: A wwpEnvPowerSwitchNotification is sent if the input power supply is switched to Battery from the AC power or switched from the Battery to the AC Power.

wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatusNotification.name: wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatusNotification
wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatusNotification.description: A wwpEnvPortalBatteryStatusNotification is sent if the Battery status changes. If the device supports the configurable battery state names, then the corresponding battery state name should also be sent with this notification.

wwpEnvPortalBatteryVoltageLevelNotificat.name: wwpEnvPortalBatteryVoltageLevelNotification
wwpEnvPortalBatteryVoltageLevelNotificat.description: A wwpEnvPortalBatteryVoltageLevelNotification is sent if the Battery voltage level changes from normal to low or vice versa. If the device supports the configurable battery state names, then the corresponding battery state name should also be sent with this notification.

wwpEnvPortalBatteryConditionNotification.name: wwpEnvPortalBatteryConditionNotification
wwpEnvPortalBatteryConditionNotification.description: A wwpEnvPortalBatteryConditionNotification is sent if the Battery condition changes from good to bad or vice versa. If the device supports the configurable battery state names, then the corresponding battery state name should also be sent with this notification.

wwpEnvPortalPowerSourceNotification.name: wwpEnvPortalPowerSourceNotification
wwpEnvPortalPowerSourceNotification.description: A wwpEnvPortalPowerSourceNotification is sent if the Battery input power source changes from battery to primary power or vice versa. A device which supports wwpEnvPowerSwitchNotification should not support this notification. If the device supports the configurable battery state names, then the corresponding battery state name should also be sent with this notification.

wwpEnvDoorStateChgNotification.name: wwpEnvDoorStateChgNotification
wwpEnvDoorStateChgNotification.description: A wwpEnvDoorStateChgNotification is sent if the door state changes.

wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateNotification.name: wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateNotification
wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateNotification.description: A wwpEnvDryContactOpenStateNotification is sent when the dry contact enters in the open state.

wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateNotification.name: wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateNotification
wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateNotification.description: A wwpEnvDryContactCloseStateNotification is sent when the dry contact enters in the close state.
